---
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Community Guidelines"
  description="Community guidelines for HyperZoneLogin channels and collaboration spaces."
  keywords={["hyperzonelogin", "community", "guidelines", "discord", "qq"]}
  canonical="/community/guidelines"
>
  <header class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 pt-32 pb-16">
    <h1 class="text-4xl leading-normal font-medium lg:text-5xl lg:leading-normal">HyperZoneLogin Community Guidelines</h1>
  </header>
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 py-4 leading-7">
    <h2 class="mb-4 text-2xl font-medium">Core Rules</h2>
    <ol class="ml-5 list-decimal space-y-2">
      <li>Be respectful. No harassment, hate speech, threats, or personal attacks.</li>
      <li>Keep discussions constructive and relevant to the project or related operations.</li>
      <li>No spam, repeated pings, or low-effort cross-posting across channels.</li>
      <li>Do not share private information or exploit details irresponsibly.</li>
      <li>Follow moderator instructions in Discord, QQ, and repository discussions.</li>
    </ol>
  </section>
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 py-4 leading-7">
    <h2 class="mb-4 text-2xl font-medium">Support and Collaboration</h2>
    <p>
      When asking for help, include versions, logs, and a clear reproduction path. This helps maintainers and community members respond
      quickly and accurately.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-3">
      If you report bugs or propose features, prefer GitHub issues with concrete context. For design-level changes, open a discussion before
      implementing large pull requests.
    </p>
  </section>
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 py-4 leading-7">
    <h2 class="mb-4 text-2xl font-medium">Enforcement</h2>
    <p>
      Moderators may remove content, mute users, or ban accounts for serious or repeated violations. Enforcement decisions prioritize project
      safety and sustainability.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-3">Last updated: <code>2026-04-12</code>.</p>
  </section>
</Layout>
